Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mongolian president Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat arrived 
in Hanoi Thursday, 3 February, at the invitation of President Le 
Duc Anh. President Ochirbat was welcomed with red carpet 
treatment at the Ba Dinh Square in Hanoi. Present at the 
ceremony, among the others, were President Le Duc Anh and 
Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam. The two presidents then 
inspected the guards of honor of the Vietnamese Army. 
Afterward, the two presidents held cordial meeting at which the 
Mongolian guest wished that the visit would help him further 
understand and learn about Vietnam's experiences in its 
renovation process. 

